                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine and careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date>19th century (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ምድ፡ for ምድጋም፡</item>
                           <item>ምቅ፡, ምቅና፡ for ምቅናይ፡</item>
                           <item>ዕዝ፡ for ዕዝል፡</item>
                           <item>ማር፡, ማርያ፡ for ማርያም፡</item>
                           <item>ም፡ for ምልጣን፡</item>
                           <item>ቅንዋ፡ for ቅንዋት፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; a few lines on the incipit page,
                           alternating with black lines; incipit of Texts I-2, I-5, I-6 and I-7;
                           names of feasts and other occasions; names of antiphons and chants, and
                           their abbreviations (e.g., qǝne, mǝqnāy, salām, mǝhǝla, mǝlṭān); initial
                           words of supplications, antiphons and other chants, and their sections
                           (e.g., sǝbḥǝwwo, täśahalänni, yǝtbārak, gǝnäyu, qalǝyä); names of the
                           categories of melody and their abbreviations (ʿǝzl, gǝʿǝz, ʾararay);
                           directives for the ministers (e.g., wa-ǝmzǝ); elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals; elements of punctuation signs.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#80v">ff. 80v-81</locus>
                           <desc>r: Praise of the virtues of haläqa Ḥagos who saved the book from
                              water, who is skilled in qǝne-poems (?). </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#80v">80v</locus>: ዝንቱ፡ ምእራፍ፡ እማየ፡ ነጠብጣብ፡ ዘአድኃኖ፡ ሃለቃ፡
                              ሐጎስ፡ ማዕምረ፡ ቅኔ፡ [<locus target="#81">81</locus>] ዘይፈጥር፡ ቅኔ፡ በዲበ፡ ምድር፡
                              አልቦ፡ ከማሁ፡ በኢትዮጵያ፡ ትጉህ፡ ለጸሎት፡ ወሰውር፡ እምኃጢአት፡ አልቦ፡ ዘአጽንአ፡ ጥበበ፡ በዲበ፡ ምድር፡
                              ከማሁ። አድኅነኒ፡ ለገብ</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The crude note stops abruptly. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title of the book is written on <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 80v, 81v.
 - Erasures: <locus target="#28ra">28ra</locus>.
 - Corrections written over erasures: e.g., <locus target="#28ra">28ra</locus>, 71rb, 74rb, 76rab, sometimes added in a
                           secondary hand, e.g., 77ra.
 - Corrections written above erasures:
                              <locus target="#7vb">7vb</locus>, 20rb.
 - Immediate corrections
                           marked by thin lines above and below the words: e.g., <locus target="#4ra">4ra</locus>, 18va, 27ra.
 - Omitted words or
                           passages written in the margin: e.g., <locus target="#6ra">6ra</locus>,
                           6va, 8vab, 9ra, 10va, 22ra.
 - Scribbles and doodles: <locus target="#59r">59r</locus>, 80r, 80v.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
